                <h2 data-uuid="19fd6fff271244cab3b62aacbf775d91"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="f4d47865f4134f2a9d38fe19158912c7">Part 2: Write a Compare and Contrast Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="49f8aec47c3d47efb147d4dbfdd57b5f">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="fb731bb82acb44c6bdf11328a3a701ad">By
                the late 1800s the U.S. had significantly expanded its presence in the world. By
                using diplomacy it gained access to markets in East Asia, and by using force it
                gained valuable territories across the globe. A nation once limited by
                isolationist policies had now grown into a powerful empire.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="8869cb8d637040f8acd864789ac83f61">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="836dfe11f9104b3799097318bba83bbb">The
                United States expanded its influence and presence in the Pacific, the
                Caribbean, and Latin America. But what motivated the United States to get
                involved in each of these regions? How were the motives similar or different
                for each geographical area? Write a compare and contrast essay to answer these
                questions.</p>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="6f99db5ac6cf4966bf4afa4609baa270">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
        <ol data-uuid="9ab3a0a0961f4a9ca685d7c98ee8c361">
            <li data-uuid="c2446eaad44f4f1885c1d79ffd0d7d20">Review your notes and sources before you start writing.</li>
            <li data-uuid="caa6be4436b04f82ba5f795e8af5ad0d">Use at least <i>two</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text or visual evidence from the documents.</li>
            <li data-uuid="15044610b7a941dda8e02f3df634d4c8">Cite specific text or visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.</li>
            <li data-uuid="0abc52bb071f41c29a84b7fa619ae051">Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.</li>
            <li data-uuid="c227463386e341069d3e8dfc2f303574">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way that highlights comparisons and contrasts.</li>
            <li data-uuid="4d86e59055134c8ca7835e963d8c5fdb">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.<br />
            </li>
        </ol>
